data.sampled:
The option strategy being implemented in this scenario is:

* Covered Call

As the seller of the $390 strike price call option, the investor is effectively selling the right for the buyer to buy 100 shares at $390 per share. In exchange for this, the investor receives a premium of $15.55 per share.

As the buyer of the $394 strike price call option, the investor is effectively buying the right to buy 100 shares at $394 per share at a later date. The premium paid for this option is $13.18 per share.

Together, these two options represent a covered call strategy, where the investor is selling calls while simultaneously buying calls, effectively neutralizing the former and generating income from the latter.
